  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Investigators hypothesized that goal-directed fluid therapy using stroke volume variation
      will improve postoperative recovery in patients undergoing free flap reconstruction after
      head and neck cancer resection. Investigators will compare the effect of goal-directed fluid
      therapy using stroke volume variation on recovery in patients undergoing free flap
      reconstruction after head and neck cancer resection.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
