  <intervention>
    <intervention_type>Procedure</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>Standard fluid therapy</intervention_name>
    <description>In Standard fluid therapy group, the administration of fluid will be guided to maintain mean blood pressure more than 65 mmHg, urine output more than 0.5 ml/kg/hr, and central venous pressure less than 14 mmHg.</description>
    <arm_group_label>Standard</arm_group_label>
  </intervention>
  <intervention>
    <intervention_type>Procedure</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>Conservative fluid therapy</intervention_name>
    <description>In Goal directed fluid therapy group, the administration of fluid will be guided by stroke volume variation. The anesthesiologist will infuse volulyte (Fresenius Kabi, Bad Homburg, Germany) 200 ml if stroke volume variation is over 12%. If cardiac index is below 2.5 l/min/m2 and stroke volume variation is below 12%, start dobutamine.</description>
    <arm_group_label>Conservative</arm_group_label>
  </intervention>
  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  adult patients of age over 20 years scheduled for free flap reconstruction after head
             and neck cancer resection

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  valvular heart disease

          -  congestive heart failure

          -  liver failure

          -  renal failure

          -  pregnant woman

          -  allergy to hydroxyethyl starch solutions

          -  coagulation abnormalities
      </textblock>
